body:
@radikalliberal
You could use a 32-bit build of the ACL and link that with the onnxruntime project.
Here you can find the documentation for how to build ACL v20.02 with a different architecture: https://arm-software.github.io/ComputeLibrary/v20.02/index.xhtml#S3_how_to_build (but you can also search for other versions)
After you build ACL you can use "--acl_home" and "--acl_libs" tags to point to the ACL home directory and the build location with the .so, respectively.

Hope this helps and sorry it took so long to respond.

@Andrews548 
thanks for the response. We did not try to dynamically link ACL, we will try that next week.
We recently also build ORT 1.5.1 with ACL 20.02 this, unfortunately, did not fix the issue.
I will update you on the outcome
